.TH SPACEGL_TELEMETRY 1 "2026-05-03" "SpaceGL 2026.05.03.01" "SpaceGL Manual"
.SH NAME
spacegl_telemetry \- SpaceGL real-time tactical telemetry client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spacegl_telemetry
[\fB\-\-tcp\fR [\fIHOST\fR]] [\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spacegl_telemetry
is a high-performance tactical monitoring tool for the SpaceGL engine.
It connects to a running
.BR spacegl_server (1)
via either a Unix Domain Socket (local) or a TCP socket (remote) to receive
a real-time binary stream of galactic asset data.
.PP
The tool features an interactive ncurses interface that organizes telemetry
into 45+ categories, including detailed per-faction ship monitors,
celestial bodies, and subspace anomalies.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-tcp \ [HOST]
Connect to the server via TCP on port 5001. If \fIHOST\fR is omitted, 
it defaults to 127.0.0.1.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B [N]
Switch to the next telemetry category.
.TP
.B [P]
Switch to the previous telemetry category.
.TP
.B [UP/DOWN]
Scroll through the entity list if it exceeds terminal height.
.TP
.B [Q]
Quit the application.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /tmp/spacegl_telemetry.sock
Default Unix Domain Socket for local IPC.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR spacegl_server (1),
.BR spacegl_diag (1),
.BR spacegl_hud (1)
